             PROBLEMS WITH CKTSIM COMPILATION

1. The evaluation tables were to big to fit through the linker, so
they have been coded in assembly. The pascal version and the assm
version should be updated in peralell allways.

2. The array calulation for table lookup, presently only done in
"clock", seems to think the array size is 34 when the correct figure
is 32. Only an assembly patch will fix. This consists of knocking out
a +1 power from the multiplication. Clock contains two of them.
On the present version:

   $41cc  is 19 s/b 00
   $4215  is 09 s/b 00

This of course would change with code changes before "clock".
